{
  "texts": [
    "Non-convergence is also caused by training the generator and discriminator in ways that are different, repetitive, and changeable.",
    "All these issues are discussed one by one in details.",
    "Convergence failureOne of the most prevalent problems with one drawback of GANs is that they often cannot settle on a solution.",
    "During GAN training, it is noticed that theoretically it is guaranteed to converge with direct alteration of the density functions; however, in practice we adjust the sample generation function G. It leads to fluctuations as a consequence.",
    "At this point in the process, the model may be trained for an extended period of time, which can provide a wide variety of categories of samples including blurry and noisy pictures."
  ]
}